England Wins Toss, Elects to Field in One-Day Game vs Sri Lanka

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-01T09:54:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/england-wins-toss-elects-to-field-in-one-day-game-vs-sri-lanka.html
England  won the toss and elected to
field in the second one-day cricket match against  Sri Lanka  at
Headingley in Leeds.  England opened the five-game series with a 110-run victory
in a rain-shortened match on June 28. The host also won a three-
Test series 1-0, while Sri Lanka scored a nine-wicket victory in
a Twenty20 match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  